HEADWORD: Coaita
<hw>Co*ai"ta</hw> <pr>(k⟦osl⟧*⟦aum⟧⟦icr⟧"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The native name of certain South
American monkeys of the genus <gen>Ateles</gen>, esp. <spn>Ateles
paniscus</spn>. The black-faced coaita is <spn>Ateles ater</spn>. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

